=09=09=09=09China on top
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Hong Kong=01,s legislature passed a law that would allow the Ch=
inese government=20
in Beijing to sack the territory=01,s leader. Pro-democracy members of the=
=20
legislature said the law eroded the autonomy of the former British colony.=
=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09A move to vote Sri Lanka=01,s minority government out of office=
 was thwarted=20
when President Chandrika Kumaratunga suspended parliament until September 7=
th.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09In a new surge of violence in Nepal, where the royal family was=
 murdered in=20
June, some 40 policemen were killed by Maoist gangs.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Japan turned down pleas by South Korea and China to correct =01=
&distortions=018 in=20
school textbooks dealing with its Asian conquests. South Korea broke off it=
s=20
(very limited) military ties with Japan.=20
