=09=09=09=09African heads of government gathered in Lusaka for the 37th and=
 final meeting=20
of the Organisation of African Unity. The group will be known in future as=
=20
the African Union, with, it is said, a commission, central bank and=20
parliament. Amara Essy, a former foreign minister of C"te d=01,Ivoire, was=
=20
elected secretary-general.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09In a breakthrough at the Burundi peace talks, chaired by Nelson=
 Mandela, the=20
country=01,s 19 political parties were said to have agreed that Pierre Buyo=
ya, a=20
Tutsi, should remain president for the first 18 months of a new three-year=
=20
transitional government. A Hutu politician would be vice-president, and the=
ir=20
roles would be reversed half-way through the term. Once a ceasefire has bee=
n=20
agreed, South Africa, Nigeria and others will send peacekeepers.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09In the latest of a string of political killings in Zambia, Paul=
 Tembo, a=20
former ally of President Frederick Chiluba who had defected to an oppositio=
n=20
party, was shot dead a few hours before he was due to testify to a corrupti=
on=20
inquiry. He had been expected to implicate several ministers.
